IMO the "bleach burnout" thing is misunderstood by many.

In the early days of drag racing bleach burnouts were used to clean,
warm and soften the tire to improve traction. These days with better
tires a "water box" is used primarily to clean the tire off and the
burnout to heat the tire takes place forward of the water box.

Light oil, soapy water, shuffle board wax or dance wax on the surface
might be a better starting point to reduce traction for a bicycle with
its low horsepower engine.

For added potential fun try a Google image search for "fire burnout".  A
bicycling video by the pre-Darwin Award folk might be in order ;-)

