Today it snowed and while I was moving some of my bikes from one shed
to another, I decided to have a go at this burning rubber business.
After making certain there was no one watching as I was sure it would
result in an embarassing fall, I lay down on my bull-horns like Graham
Obree on my 48x18 fixed and started pedalling on my snow dusted lawn. I
didn't get very far, but lots of wheelspin! My attempt was by no means
anywhere near the results from the kid in the video, but I am confident
that with practice, snow dusted grass would be a suitable surface to do
this trick. The moral of the story is that I think there are many
different surfaces that this can be done on.

